233/* Function: swap ===========================================



234 * Abstract:



235 *      Function to swap two numbers



236 */



237inline void swap(char *first, char *second) {



238	char temp = *first; *first = *second; *second = temp;



239}



240



241/* Function: reverse ===========================================



242 * Abstract:



243 *      Function to reverse the elements of array



244 */



245char* reverse(char *array, int begin, int end)



246{



247	while (begin < end)



248		swap(&array[begin++], &array[end--]);



249



250	return array;



251}



252



253/* Function: itoa ===========================================



254 * Abstract:



255 *      Function to convert the integer value to char.



256 */



257char* itoa(int value, char* array, int base)



258{



259	// invalid base type - not supported



260	if (base < 2 || base > 32)



261		return array;



262



263	// Use the absolute value of the input number



264	int absVal = abs(value);



265



266	int i = 0;



267	while (absVal)



268	{



269		int r = absVal % base;



270



271		if (r >= 10) 



272			array[i++] = 65 + (r - 10);



273		else



274			array[i++] = 48 + r;



275



276		absVal = absVal / base;



277	}



278



279	// If number is 0 send the '0' char



280	if (i == 0)



281		array[i++] = '0';



282



283	// Only for the base 10 system, add '-' before the number 



284	// for negative numbers. For other base system consider 



285	// the number as unsigned.



286	if (value < 0 && base == 10)



287		array[i++] = '-';



288



289	array[i] = '\0'; // Add a null terminator



290



291	// Revserse the string before returning



292	return reverse(array, 0, i - 1);



293}



294#endif // MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY

297/* Function: staticAlloc ===========================================



298 * Abstract:



299 *      Allocate static memory from predefined array.



300 */



301static void* staticAlloc(size_t size)



302{



303    void* retPtr = NULL;



304    static uint8_T circBufCounter = 0;



305	



306    #if MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_SIZE > 0



307    uint32_T alignvalue = 0;



308	



309    



310    if (circBufCounter == 0)



311    {



312        /* Initialize the Pointer */



313        circBufPointer = circularBuffer1;



314        memset(circBufPointer, 0, MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_SIZE);



315        circBufCounter = 1;



316    }



317    



318    if((circBufPointer + size) < (circularBuffer1 + MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_SIZE))



319    {



320        retPtr = circBufPointer;



321        circBufPointer = circBufPointer + size;



322        



323        



324        if(sizeof(uint16_T) == 2)



325        {



326            //PX4 is 32 bit targets



327            alignvalue = (uint32_T)circBufPointer % 8;



328            circBufPointer = (alignvalue != 0) ? (circBufPointer + (8 - alignvalue)): circBufPointer;



329        }



330        else if(sizeof(uint16_T) == 1)



331        {



332            //TI is 16 bit targets



333            alignvalue = (uint32_T)circBufPointer % 4;



334            circBufPointer = (alignvalue != 0) ? (circBufPointer + (4 - alignvalue)): circBufPointer;



335        }



336    }



337    else



338    {



339        retPtr = NULL;



340        circBufPointer = NULL;



341        circBufCounter = 2;



342    }



343    #endif



344    return retPtr;



345}



346#endif

348/* Function: rt_BytePack8bit ===========================================



349 * Abstract:



350 *      Pack the data into 8-bit packets.



351 */



352static int rt_BytePack8bit(char* outdata, char* inport, int inportWidth, int typeLen)



353{



354    int i, j;



355    int k = 0;



356    /* number of words (16 bit length) to send */



357    int numWrd = (inportWidth * typeLen) / 2;



358



359    /* Little Endian, 8bit swap */



360    for (i = 0; i < numWrd; i++) {



361        for (j = 0; j < 2; j++) {



362            outdata[k++] = (inport[i] >> (8*j)) & 255;



363        }



364    }



365    return (inportWidth * typeLen);



366}

368/* Function: rt_PacketWrite ===========================================



369 * Abstract:



370 *      Pack the data into a temporary buffer before writing it to the file.



371 */



372static int rt_PacketWrite(FILE *fp, char* inport, uint16_T inSize)



373{



374    uint16_T loopCount = inSize / BUFFERSIZE;



375    uint16_T offset = inSize % BUFFERSIZE;



376    int packet, packetSize = 0;



377    for (packet = 0; packet < loopCount; packet++)



378    {



379        packetSize = packetSize + rt_BytePack8bit((char*)tempBuffer, inport, 1, BUFFERSIZE);



380        if ( MW_fwrite(tempBuffer, 1, BUFFERSIZE, fp) !=



381                ((size_t) BUFFERSIZE) )



382        {



383            bStopLogging = 1;



384            return(1);



385        }



386        inport = inport + (BUFFERSIZE / 2);



387    }



388    if (offset > 0)



389    {



390        packetSize = packetSize + rt_BytePack8bit((char*)tempBuffer, inport, 1, offset);



391        if ( MW_fwrite(tempBuffer, 1, offset, fp) !=



392                ((size_t) offset) )



393        {



394            bStopLogging = 1;



395            return(1);



396        }



397    }



398    return packetSize;



399}

533/* Function: rt_GetDblValueFromOverSizedData ===================================



534 * Abstract:



535 */



536static double rt_GetDblValueFromOverSizedData(



537        const void *pVoid,



538        int bitsPerChunk,



539        int numOfChunk,



540        unsigned int isSigned,



541        double fracSlope,



542        int fixedExp,



543        double bias)



544{



545    double retValue = 0;



546    



547    double *dblValue = (double *) calloc(numOfChunk, sizeof(double));



548    



549    int i;



550    double isSignedNeg;



551    



552    if(isSigned) {



553        const chunk_T *pData = (const chunk_T *) (pVoid);



554        for (i = 0; i <numOfChunk; i++) {



555            dblValue[i] = (double)(pData[i]);



556        }



557    } else  {



558        const uchunk_T *pData = (const uchunk_T *) (pVoid);



559        for (i = 0; i <numOfChunk; i++) {



560            dblValue[i] = (double)(pData[i]);



561        }



562    }



563    



564    /*



565     * Assuming multi chunks b_n ... b_2 b_1 b_0, and the length of each chunk is N.



566     * Suppose b_i is the i-th chunk's value.



567     * Then for unsigned data or data with one chunk: we have



568     * retValue = b_n * 2^(n*N) + ... + b_1 * 2^N + b_0 * 2^0;



569     * But for signed data, we have



570     * retValue = b_n * 2^(n*N) + ... + b_1 * 2^N + b_0 * 2^0+ (b_0<0) * 2^N +



571     * ... (b_(n-1) <0) * 2^(n*N)



572     * = (b_n + (b_(n-1)<0)) * 2^(n*N) +... + (b_1 + (b_0<0)) * 2^N + b_0 * 2^0;



573     * Together:



574     * retValue =



575     * (b_n + isSigned * (b_(n-1)<0)) * 2^(n*N) +... + (b_1 + isSigned * (b_0<0)) * 2^N + b_0 * 2^0;



576     */



577    



578    retValue = dblValue[numOfChunk - 1];



579    



580    for(i = numOfChunk - 1; i > 0; i--) {



581        isSignedNeg = dblValue[i - 1] < 0 ? (double)isSigned : 0;



582        retValue = retValue + isSignedNeg;



583        



584        retValue = ldexp(retValue, bitsPerChunk)+ dblValue[i-1];



585    }



586    retValue = ldexp( fracSlope * retValue, fixedExp ) + bias;



587    



588    FREE(dblValue);



589    return (retValue);



590    



591} /* end rt_GetDblValueFromOverSizedData */

594/* Function: rt_GetNonBoolMxIdFromDTypeId ======================================



595 * Abstract:



596 *      Get the mx???_CLASS given the simulink builtin data type id.



597 */



598static mxClassID rt_GetNonBoolMxIdFromDTypeId(BuiltInDTypeId dTypeID)



599{



600    mxClassID mxID;



601    



602    switch (dTypeID) {



603        case SS_DOUBLE:



604            mxID = (sizeof(real_T)== sizeof(real32_T)? mxSINGLE_CLASS: mxDOUBLE_CLASS);



605            break;



606        case SS_SINGLE:



607            mxID = mxSINGLE_CLASS;



608            break;



609        case SS_INT8:



610            switch (sizeof(int8_T)) {



611                case 4: /* PWS - int8_T mapped to 32-bits */



612                    mxID = mxINT32_CLASS;



613                    break;



614                case 2: /* PWS - int8_T mapped to 16-bits */



615                    mxID = mxINT16_CLASS;



616                    break;



617                case 1:



618                    mxID = mxINT8_CLASS;



619                    break;



620                default:



621                    mxID = mxUNKNOWN_CLASS;



622                    break;



623            }



624            break;



625        case SS_UINT8:



626            switch (sizeof(uint8_T)) {



627                case 4: /* PWS - uint8_T mapped to 32-bits */



628                    mxID = mxUINT32_CLASS;



629                    break;



630                case 2: /* PWS - uint8_T mapped to 16-bits */



631                    mxID = mxUINT16_CLASS;



632                    break;



633                case 1:



634                    mxID = mxUINT8_CLASS;



635                    break;



636                default:



637                    mxID = mxUNKNOWN_CLASS;



638                    break;



639            }



640            break;



641        case SS_INT16:



642            mxID = (sizeof(int16_T)==4? mxINT32_CLASS: mxINT16_CLASS);



643            break;



644        case SS_UINT16:



645            mxID = (sizeof(uint16_T)==4? mxUINT32_CLASS: mxUINT16_CLASS);



646            break;



647        case SS_INT32:



648            mxID = mxINT32_CLASS;



649            break;



650        case SS_UINT32:



651            mxID = mxUINT32_CLASS;



652            break;



653            /*case SS_BOOLEAN:



654             * mxID = (sizeof(boolean_T)==4? mxUINT32_CLASS: mxLOGICAL_CLASS);



655             * break;*/



656        default:



657            mxID = mxUNKNOWN_CLASS;



658            break;



659    }



660    



661    return(mxID);



662    



663} /* end rt_GetNonBoolMxIdFromDTypeId */

3613/* Function: rt_WriteItemToMatFile =============================================



3614 * Abstract:



3615 *      Entry function for writing out a mat item to the mat file.



3616 *



3617 *      Return values is



3618 *          == 0 : upon success



3619 *          <> 0 : upon failure



3620 */



3621static int_T rt_WriteItemToMatFile(FILE         *fp,



3622        MatItem      *pItem,



3623        ItemDataKind itemKind,



3624        uint8_T packetWrite)



3625{



3626    /* Determine the item size */



3627    if (pItem->type == matMATRIX) {



3628    #ifdef MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



3629        if (rt_ProcessMatItemSizeCalculate(fp, pItem, itemKind)) return(1);



3630    #else



3631        if (rt_ProcessMatItem(fp, pItem, itemKind, 0)) return(1);



3632    #endif //MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



3633    }



3634    



3635    /* Write the item tag and data */



3636    if (pItem->nbytes > 4) {



3637        int32_T nAlignBytes;



3638



3639        if (sizeof(uint16_T) == 1)



3640        {



3641            /* For 16-bit processor. Split the data into 8-bit packets and write into file */



3642            if(rt_PacketWrite(fp, (char*)pItem, matTAG_SIZE) !=



3643                    ((size_t) matTAG_SIZE)) {



3644                bStopLogging = 1;



3645                return(1);



3646            }



3647        }



3648        else



3649        {



3650            if ( MW_fwrite(pItem, 1, matTAG_SIZE, fp) !=



3651                    ((size_t) matTAG_SIZE) ) {



3652                bStopLogging = 1;



3653                return(1);



3654            }



3655        }



3656        



3657        if (pItem->type == matMATRIX) {



3658            #ifdef MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



3659		switch (itemKind) {



3660			case MATRIX_ITEM: {



3661					if (rt_ProcessMatItemWriteFileMatrixItem(fp, pItem, itemKind))



3662					{



3663						bStopLogging =1;



3664						return(1);



3665					}



3666					break;



3667				}



3668				case SIGNALS_STRUCT_ITEM: {



3669					if (rt_ProcessMatItemWriteFileSignalStructItem(fp, pItem, itemKind))



3670					{



3671						bStopLogging =1;



3672						return(1);



3673					}



3674					break;



3675				}



3676				



3677				default: {			



3678					if (rt_ProcessMatItemWriteFile(fp, pItem, itemKind))



3679					{



3680						bStopLogging =1;



3681						return(1);



3682					}



3683					break;



3684				}



3685			}



3686            #else



3687            if (rt_ProcessMatItem(fp, pItem, itemKind, 1))



3688            {



3689                bStopLogging =1;



3690                return(1);



3691            }



3692            #endif //MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



3693	}



3694        else



3695        {



3696            if (packetWrite == 1)



3697            {



3698                /* For 16-bit processor. Split the data into 8-bit packets and write into file */



3699                if(rt_PacketWrite(fp, (char*)pItem->data, pItem->nbytes) !=



3700                        ((size_t) pItem->nbytes)) {



3701                    bStopLogging = 1;



3702                    return(1);



3703                }



3704            }



3705            else



3706            {



3707                if ( MW_fwrite(pItem->data, 1, pItem->nbytes, fp) !=



3708                        ((size_t) pItem->nbytes) ) {



3709                    bStopLogging = 1;



3710                    return(1);



3711                }



3712            }



3713        }



3714        



3715        /* Add offset for 8-byte alignment */



3716        nAlignBytes = matINT64_ALIGN(pItem->nbytes) - pItem->nbytes;



3717        if (nAlignBytes > 0) {



3718            int pad[8] = {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0};



3719            if ( MW_fwrite(pad,1,nAlignBytes,fp) != ((size_t) nAlignBytes) ) {



3720                bStopLogging = 1;



3721                return(1);



3722            }



3723        }



3724    } else {



3725        MatItem item = {0, 0, NULL};



3726        item.type = ((uint32_T)(pItem->type))|(((uint32_T)(pItem->nbytes))<<16);



3727        (void)memcpy(&item.nbytes, pItem->data, pItem->nbytes);



3728        if (sizeof(uint16_T) == 1)



3729        {



3730			if (packetWrite == 1)



3731			{



3732				/* For 16-bit processor. Split the data into 8-bit packets and write into file */



3733				if(rt_PacketWrite(fp, (char*)&item, matTAG_SIZE) !=



3734						((size_t) matTAG_SIZE)) {



3735					bStopLogging = 1;



3736					return(1);



3737				}



3738			}



3739			else



3740			{



3741				/* For 16-bit processor. Split the data into 8-bit packets and write into file */



3742				if(rt_PacketWrite(fp, (char*)&item, 4) != ((size_t) 4) ||



3743					 ( MW_fwrite(&item.nbytes, 1, 4, fp) != ((size_t) 4) )) {



3744					bStopLogging = 1;



3745					return(1);



3746				}



3747			}



3748        }



3749        else



3750        {



3751            if ( MW_fwrite(&item, 1, matTAG_SIZE, fp) !=



3752                    ((size_t) matTAG_SIZE) ) {



3753                bStopLogging = 1;



3754                return(1);



3755            }



3756        }



3757    }



3758    



3759    return(0);



3760    



3761} /* end rt_WriteItemToMatFile */

3764/* Function: rt_WriteMat5FileHeader ============================================



3765 * Abstract:



3766 *      Function to write the mat file header.



3767 *      Return values is



3768 *          == 0 : upon success



3769 *          <> 0 : upon failure



3770 */



3771static int_T rt_WriteMat5FileHeader(FILE *fp)



3772{



3773    int_T        nbytes;



3774    int_T        nspaces;



3775    int_T        i, n;



3776    unsigned short ver[2];



3777    char_T       spaces[16];



3778    const char_T *matversion = "MATLAB 5.0 MAT-file";



3779    



3780    (void)memset(spaces, ' ', sizeof(spaces));



3781    



3782    n = (int_T)strlen(matversion);



3783    nbytes = (int_T)MW_fwrite(matversion, 1, n, fp);



3784    /*LINTED E_ASSIGN_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/



3785    nspaces = matVERSION_INFO_OFFSET - nbytes;



3786    /*LINTED E_ASSIGN_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/



3787    n = nspaces % sizeof(spaces);



3788    nbytes += (int_T)MW_fwrite(spaces, 1, n, fp);



3789    /*LINTED E_ASSIGN_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/



3790    n = nspaces / sizeof(spaces);



3791    for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {



3792        nbytes += (int_T)MW_fwrite(spaces, 1, sizeof(spaces), fp);



3793    }



3794    if (nbytes == matVERSION_INFO_OFFSET) {



3795        ver[0] = matVERSION;



3796        ver[1] = matKEY;



3797



3798        if (sizeof(uint16_T) == 1)



3799        {



3800            /* For 16-bit processor. Split the data into 8-bit packets and write into file */



3801            nbytes += (int_T)rt_PacketWrite(fp, (char*)ver, sizeof(ver) * PROCESSOR_BASE_TYPE_SIZE);



3802        }



3803        else



3804        {



3805            nbytes += (int_T)MW_fwrite(ver, 1, sizeof(ver) * PROCESSOR_BASE_TYPE_SIZE, fp);



3806        }



3807    }



3808    return(nbytes != matVERSION_INFO_OFFSET + (sizeof(ver) * PROCESSOR_BASE_TYPE_SIZE));



3809    



3810} /* end rt_WriteMat5FileHeader */

3813/* Function: rt_FixupLogVar ====================================================

3817static const char_T *rt_FixupLogVar(LogVar *var,int verbose)



3818{

4015/* Function: rt_LoadModifiedLogVarName =========================================



4016 * Abstract:



4017 *      The name of the logged variable is obtained from the input argument



4018 *      varName and the nameModifier which is obtained from the simstruct. If



4019 *      the nameModifier begins with an '_', then nameModifier is post-pended to



4020 *      varName to obtain the name of the logged variable. If the first

4023 *



4024 * Examples:



4025 *     a)  varName = "tout" & nameModifier = "_rt"  => logVarName = "tout_rt"



4026 *     b)  varName = "tout" & nameModifier = "rt_"  => logVarName = "rt_tout"



4027 *     c)  varName = "tout" & nameModifier = "none" => logVarName = "tout"



4028 */



4029static void rt_LoadModifiedLogVarName(const RTWLogInfo *li,         /* in  */



4030        const char       *varName,    /* in  */



4031        char             *logVarName) /* out */



4032{



4033    int_T        nameLen;



4034    const char_T *nameModifier = rtliGetLogVarNameModifier(li);



4035    



4036    if (nameModifier != NULL && strcmp(nameModifier,"none")==0) {



4037        nameModifier = NULL;



4038    }



4039    



4040    logVarName[mxMAXNAM-1] = '\0';



4041    if (nameModifier == NULL) {



4042        (void)strncpy(logVarName, varName, mxMAXNAM-1);



4043    } else if (nameModifier[0] == '_') {



4044        (void)strncpy(logVarName, varName, mxMAXNAM-1);



4045        nameLen = (int_T)strlen(logVarName);



4046        (void)strncat(logVarName, nameModifier, mxMAXNAM-1-nameLen);



4047    } else {



4048        (void)strncpy(logVarName, nameModifier, mxMAXNAM-1);



4049        nameLen = (int_T)strlen(logVarName);



4050        (void)strncat(logVarName, varName, mxMAXNAM-1-nameLen);



4051    }



4052    



4053} /* end rt_LoadModifiedLogVarName */

4617                (int_T)strlen(stateNames[sigIdx]);

4620                }

4632            mtxData->dims    = mtxData->_dims;



4633            mtxData->dims[0] = mtxData->nCols;



4634

4636            mtxData->im      = NULL;



4637            mtxData->dTypeID = SS_INT16;



4638            mtxData->mxID    = mxCHAR_CLASS;



4639            mtxData->elSize  = sizeof(short);



4640            mtxData->logical = 0U;



4641            mtxData->complex = 0U;

4644        }

4646        



4647        if(logValueDimensions){



4648            sig->fieldNames = rtGlobalLoggingSignalsStructFieldNames;



4649        }

4652        }

4662        



4663        if (overhang) {



4664            dataOffset += (sizeof(real_T) - overhang);



4665        }

4673        #endif

4675        data = (real_T*) (((char_T*) (sig->crossMdlRef)) + dataOffset);



4676        



4677        for(sigIdx=0;sigIdx<nSignals;sigIdx++) {



4678            data[sigIdx] = crossMdlRef[sigIdx];



4679        }



4680        



4681        for (i = 0; i < nSignals; i++) {



4682            MatrixData *mtxData = &(sig->crossMdlRef[i]);



4683            



4684            (void)memcpy(mtxData->name, &CROSS_MDL_REF_FIELD_NAME, mxMAXNAM);



4685            mtxData->nRows   = 1;



4686            mtxData->nCols   = 1;



4687            mtxData->nDims   = 1; /* => matlab scalar */



4688            



4689            mtxData->re      = &data[i];



4690            mtxData->im      = NULL;



4691            mtxData->dTypeID = (sizeof(real_T)== sizeof(real32_T)? SS_SINGLE: SS_DOUBLE);



4692            mtxData->mxID    = rt_GetMxIdFromDTypeId(SS_DOUBLE);



4693            mtxData->elSize  = sizeof(real_T);



4694            mtxData->logical = matLOGICAL_BIT;



4695            mtxData->complex = 0U;

4703    



4704    ERROR_EXIT:

4707        statusMessage = SIGNALSTRUCTURECREATEERROR;



4708        #else

4710                "in the struct log variable %s\n", var->name);



4711        #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE

4731/* Function: local_CreateStructLogVar ==========================================

4736 *      ~= NULL  => success, returns the log variable created.



4737 *      == NULL  => failure, error message set in the simstruct.

4739static StructLogVar *local_CreateStructLogVar(



4740        RTWLogInfo              *li,



4741        const real_T            startTime,



4742        const real_T            finalTime,



4743        const real_T            inStepSize,



4744        const char_T            **errStatus,



4745        const char_T            *varName,



4746        boolean_T               logTime,



4747        int_T                   maxRows,



4748        int_T                   decimation,



4749        real_T                  sampleTime,

4761    #else

4763    #endif

4775                inStepSize, errStatus,

4780                NULL, NULL, maxRows,



4781                decimation, sampleTime, 0);

4786        size_t         nbytes = sizeof(MatrixData);

4788

4797        time->nRows   = 0;



4798        time->nCols   = 0;

4813                var,maxRows,decimation,sampleTime,sigInfo)) {

4816    }

4818    /* blockName Field */

4820        int_T  dataLen = (int_T)strlen(blockName);



4821        size_t nbytes;



4822        size_t dataOffset = sizeof(MatrixData);



4823        /*LINTED E_ASSIGN_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/



4824        uint_T overhang   = (uint_T)(dataOffset % sizeof(short));



4825        



4826        if (overhang) {



4827            dataOffset += (sizeof(short) - overhang);



4828        }



4829        /*LINTED E_ASSIGN_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/



4830        nbytes = dataOffset + dataLen*sizeof(short);



4831



4832        #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



4833        if ( (var->blockName = staticAlloc(nbytes)) == NULL ) goto ERROR_EXIT;

4835        if ( (var->blockName = calloc(nbytes, 1)) == NULL ) goto ERROR_EXIT;



4836        #endif

4851                data[i] = (uint8_T)blockName[i];

4855        var->blockName->im      = NULL;



4856        var->blockName->dTypeID = SS_INT16;



4857        var->blockName->mxID    = mxCHAR_CLASS;



4858        var->blockName->elSize  = sizeof(short);



4859        var->blockName->logical = 0U;



4860        var->blockName->complex = 0U;

4866    {



4867        StructLogVar *list = logInfo->structLogVarsList;



4868        



4869        if (list != NULL) {



4870            while (list->next != NULL) {



4871                list = list->next;



4872            }



4873            list->next = var;



4874        } else {



4875            logInfo->structLogVarsList = var;



4876        }



4877    }



4878    



4879    return(var); /* NORMAL_EXIT */



4880    



4881    ERROR_EXIT:



4882        #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



4883        statusMessage = LOGVARCREATEERROR;



4884        #else



4885        (void)fprintf(stderr, "*** Error creating log variable %s\n", varName);



4886        #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



4887        if (*errStatus == NULL) {



4888            *errStatus = rtMemAllocError;



4889        }



4890        #ifndef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



4891        rt_DestroyStructLogVar(var);



4892        #endif



4893        return(NULL);



4894        



4895} /* end local_CreateStructLogVar */

4951        #endif



4952                *errStatus = rtMemAllocError;



4953                goto ERROR_EXIT;



4954            }



4955        }



4956

4960

5000

5066/* Function: rt_ReallocLogVar ==================================================



5067 * Abstract:



5068 *   Allocate more memory for the data buffers in the log variable.



5069 *   Exit if unable to allocate more memory.



5070 */



5071static void rt_ReallocLogVar(LogVar *var, boolean_T isVarDims)



5072{



5073    void *tmp;



5074    int_T nCols = var->data.nCols;



5075    int_T nRows = var->data.nRows + DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE;



5076    size_t elSize = var->data.elSize;



5077    



5078    tmp = realloc(var->data.re, nRows*nCols*elSize);



5079    if (tmp == NULL) {



5080        #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5081        statusMessage = MEMORYALLOCATIONERROR;



5082        #else



5083        (void)fprintf(stderr,



5084                "*** Memory allocation error.\n");



5085        (void)fprintf(stderr, ""



5086                "    varName          = %s%s\n"



5087                "    nRows            = %d\n"



5088                "    nCols            = %d\n"



5089                "    elementSize      = %lu\n"



5090                "    Current Size     = %.16g\n"



5091                "    Failed resize    = %.16g\n\n",



5092                var->data.name,



5093                var->data.complex ? " (real part)" : "",



5094                        var->data.nRows,



5095                        var->data.nCols,



5096                        (long)  var->data.elSize,



5097                        (double)nRows*nCols*elSize,



5098                        (double)(nRows+DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE)*nCols*elSize);



5099        #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5100                exit(1);



5101    }



5102    var->data.re = tmp;



5103    



5104    if (var->data.complex) {



5105        tmp = realloc(var->data.im, nRows*nCols*elSize);



5106        if (tmp == NULL) {



5107            #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5108            statusMessage = MEMORYALLOCATIONERROR;



5109            #else



5110            (void)fprintf(stderr,



5111                    "*** Memory allocation error.\n");



5112            (void)fprintf(stderr, ""



5113                    "    varName          = %s (complex part)\n"



5114                    "    nRows            = %d\n"



5115                    "    nCols            = %d\n"



5116                    "    elementSize      = %lu\n"



5117                    "    Current Size     = %.16g\n"



5118                    "    Failed resize    = %.16g\n\n",



5119                    var->data.name,



5120                    var->data.nRows,



5121                    var->data.nCols,



5122                    (long)  var->data.elSize,



5123                    (double)nRows*nCols*elSize,



5124                    (double)(nRows+DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE)*nCols*elSize);



5125            #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5126            exit(1);



5127        }



5128        var->data.im = tmp;



5129    }



5130    var->data.nRows = nRows;



5131    



5132    /* Also reallocate memory for "valueDimensions"



5133     * when logging the variable-size signal



5134     */



5135    if(isVarDims){



5136        int_T k;



5137        



5138        nCols = var->valDims->nCols;



5139        nRows = var->valDims->nRows + DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE;



5140        elSize = sizeof(real_T);



5141        tmp = realloc(var->valDims->dimsData, nRows*nCols*elSize);



5142        if (tmp == NULL) {



5143            #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5144            statusMessage = MEMORYALLOCATIONERROR;



5145            #else



5146            (void)fprintf(stderr,



5147                    "*** Memory allocation error.\n");



5148            (void)fprintf(stderr, ""



5149                    "    varName          = %s\n"



5150                    "    nRows            = %d\n"



5151                    "    nCols            = %d\n"



5152                    "    elementSize      = %lu\n"



5153                    "    Current Size     = %.16g\n"



5154                    "    Failed resize    = %.16g\n\n",



5155                    var->valDims->name,



5156                    var->valDims->nRows,



5157                    var->valDims->nCols,



5158                    (long)  elSize,



5159                    (double)nRows*nCols*elSize,



5160                    (double)(nRows+DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE)*nCols*elSize);



5161            #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5162            exit(1);



5163        }



5164        



5165        /*



5166         * valueDimensions data is stored in array format and must be



5167         * adjusted after reallocation (see also rt_FixupLogVar())



5168         *



5169         * Example: maxRows = 4; nRows = 4; nDims = 3;



5170         * Before realloc of the logVar, the locations of data are as below:



5171         * (x, y, z -- useful data / o -- junk, don't care)



5172         * a[0] = x    a[4] = y    a[8] = z



5173         * a[1] = x    a[5] = y    a[9] = z



5174         * a[2] = x    a[6] = y    a[10]= z



5175         * a[3] = x    a[7] = y    a[11]= z



5176         *



5177         * After realloc of the logVar (suppose 2 extra rows are added),



5178         * the locations of data are as below:



5179         * a[0] = x    a[6] = y    a[12]= o



5180         * a[1] = x    a[7] = y    a[13]= o



5181         * a[2] = x    a[8] = z    a[14]= o



5182         * a[3] = x    a[9] = z    a[15]= o



5183         * a[4] = y    a[10]= z    a[16]= o



5184         * a[5] = y    a[11]= z    a[17]= o



5185         *



5186         * The data must be adjusted as below:



5187         * a[0] = x    a[6] = y    a[12]= z



5188         * a[1] = x    a[7] = y    a[13]= z



5189         * a[2] = x    a[8] = y    a[14]= z



5190         * a[3] = x    a[9] = y    a[15]= z



5191         * a[4] = o    a[10]= o    a[16]= o



5192         * a[5] = o    a[11]= o    a[17]= o



5193         */



5194        for(k = var->data.nDims-1; k > 0; k--){



5195            (void) memcpy((real_T*)tmp + k*nRows,



5196                    (real_T*)tmp + k*var->valDims->nRows,



5197                    elSize * var->valDims->nRows);



5198        }



5199        



5200        var->valDims->dimsData = tmp;



5201        var->valDims->nRows = nRows;



5202    }



5203    



5204} /* end rt_ReallocLogVar */

5207/* Function: rt_UpdateLogVarWithDiscontiguousData ==============================



5208 * Abstract:



5209 *      Log one row of the LogVar with data that is not contiguous.



5210 */



5211static void rt_UpdateLogVarWithDiscontiguousData(LogVar            *var,



5212        LogSignalPtrsType data,



5213        const int_T       *segmentLengths,



5214        int_T             nSegments)



5215{



5216    size_t elSize = 0;



5217    size_t offset = 0;



5218    int    segIdx = 0;



5219    



5220    if(bStopLogging ==0)



5221    {



5222        if (++var->numHits % var->decimation) return;



5223        var->numHits = 0;



5224        



5225        /*



5226         * Reallocate or wrap the LogVar



5227         */



5228        if (((var->rowIdx == ((var->data.nRows)/2)) && !(var->wrapped == var->data.nRows+1)) || ((var->rowIdx == var->data.nRows) && !(var->wrapped == -1))) {



5229            /* Check the wrapped variable to ensure that the bDataReady is not getting triggered by the var which missed bDataReady before */



5230            bDataReady = 1;



5231        }



5232        



5233        if(bDataReady ==1) /* switching to the other half of the ping-pong */



5234        {



5235            if (var->wrapped == -2)



5236            {



5237                var->rowIdx = 0; /* Needs to switch to ping, this var didn't see bDataReady */



5238                var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



5239            }



5240            else if ((!((var->wrapped == -1) || (var->wrapped == (var->data.nRows + 1)) ))&& ((var->wrapped < (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx < (var->data.nRows)/2))) /* wrapped and rowIdx are in the ping */



5241            {



5242                var->rowIdx = ((var->data.nRows)/2); /* switching to pong */



5243            }



5244            else if ((!((var->wrapped == -1) || (var->wrapped == (var->data.nRows + 1)) )) && ((var->wrapped >= (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx >= (var->data.nRows)/2))) /* wrapped and rowIdx are in the pong */



5245            {



5246                var->rowIdx = 0; /* switching to ping */



5247            }



5248            else if (((var->wrapped < (var->data.nRows)/2)  || (var->wrapped == (var->data.nRows + 1))) && (var->rowIdx == var->data.nRows)) /* check if the rowIdx is not crossing boundaries */



5249            {



5250                var->rowIdx = (var->data.nRows)/2;



5251            }



5252            else if (((var->wrapped >= (var->data.nRows)/2) || (var->wrapped == -1)) && (var->rowIdx == var->data.nRows/2)) /*check if the rowIdx is not crossing boundaries */



5253            {



5254                var->rowIdx = 0;



5255            }



5256        }



5257        else if (var->wrapped == -2)



5258        {



5259            var->rowIdx = 0; /* Needs to switch to ping, this var didn't see bDataReady */



5260            var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



5261        }



5262        else if ((var->wrapped < (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx >= (var->data.nRows)/2)) /* wrapped is in the ping, rowIdx in the pong */



5263        {



5264            var->rowIdx = 0; /* Needs to switch to ping, this var didn't see bDataReady */



5265            var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



5266        }



5267        else if ((var->wrapped >= (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx < (var->data.nRows)/2)) /* wrapped is in the pong, rowIdx in the ping */



5268        {



5269            var->rowIdx = ((var->data.nRows)/2); /* Needs to switch to pong, this var didn't see bDataReady */



5270            var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



5271        }



5272        else



5273        {



5274            var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



5275        }



5276        



5277        /* This function is only used to log states, there's no var-dims issue. */



5278        elSize = var->data.elSize;



5279        offset = (size_t)(elSize * var->rowIdx * var->data.nCols);



5280        



5281        if (var->data.complex) {



5282            char_T *dstRe = (char_T*)(var->data.re) + offset;



5283            char_T *dstIm = (char_T*)(var->data.im) + offset;



5284            



5285            for (segIdx = 0; segIdx < nSegments; segIdx++) {



5286                int_T         nEl  = segmentLengths[segIdx];



5287                const  char_T *src = (const void *)data[segIdx];



5288                int_T         el;



5289                



5290                for (el = 0; el < nEl; el++) {



5291                    (void)memcpy(dstRe, src, elSize);



5292                    dstRe += elSize;   src += elSize;



5293                    (void)memcpy(dstIm, src, elSize);



5294                    dstIm += elSize;   src += elSize;



5295                }



5296            }



5297        } else {



5298            char_T *dst = (char_T*)(var->data.re) + offset;



5299            



5300            for (segIdx = 0; segIdx < nSegments; segIdx++) {



5301                size_t      segSize = elSize*segmentLengths[segIdx];



5302                const  void *src    = data[segIdx];



5303                



5304                (void)memcpy(dst, src, segSize);



5305                dst += segSize;



5306            }



5307        }



5308        



5309        ++var->rowIdx;



5310    }



5311    return;



5312    



5313} /* end rt_UpdateLogVarWithDiscontiguousData */

5322#ifdef __cplusplus



5323extern "C" {



5324#endif



5325    



5326    



5327    /* Function: rt_CreateLogVarWithConvert ========================================



5328     * Abstract:



5329     *	Create a logging variable.



5330     *



5331     * Returns:



5332     *	~= NULL  => success, returns the log variable created.



5333     *	== NULL  => failure, error message set in the simstruct.



5334     */



5335    LogVar *rt_CreateLogVarWithConvert(



5336            RTWLogInfo        *li,



5337            const real_T      startTime,



5338            const real_T      finalTime,



5339            const real_T      inStepSize,



5340            const char_T      **errStatus,



5341            const char_T      *varName,



5342            BuiltInDTypeId    inpDataTypeID,



5343            const RTWLogDataTypeConvert *pDataTypeConvertInfo,



5344            int_T             logical,



5345            int_T             complex,



5346            int_T             frameData,



5347            int_T             nCols,



5348            int_T             nDims,



5349            const int_T       *dims,



5350            LogValDimsStat    logValDimsStat,



5351            void              **currSigDims,



5352            int_T             *currSigDimsSize,



5353            int_T             maxRows,



5354            int_T             decimation,



5355            real_T            sampleTime,



5356            int_T             appendToLogVarsList)



5357    {



5358        int_T          usingDefaultBufSize = 0;



5359#ifdef NO_LOGGING_REALLOC



5360        int_T          okayToRealloc       = 0;



5361#else



5362        int_T          okayToRealloc       = 1;



5363#endif



5364        LogVar         *var                = NULL;



5365        /*inpDataTypeID is the rt_LoggedOutputDataTypeId*/



5366        BuiltInDTypeId dTypeID             = (BuiltInDTypeId)inpDataTypeID;



5367        size_t         elementSize         = rt_GetSizeofDataType(dTypeID);



5368        int_T          frameSize;



5369        int_T          nRows;



5370        int_T          nColumns;



5371        



5372        /*===================================================================*



5373         * Determine the frame size if the data is frame based               *



5374         *===================================================================*/



5375        frameSize = frameData ? dims[0] : 1;



5376        



5377        /*===================================================================*



5378         * Calculate maximum number of rows needed in the buffer             *



5379         *===================================================================*/



5380        



5381        if ((finalTime > startTime) || (finalTime == -1) ||  (finalTime == rtInf)) {



5382            real_T nPoints;            /* Tfinal is finite  ===>  nRows can be  */



5383            real_T stepSize;           /* computed since the StepSize is fixed  */



5384            real_T finalTimeTemp;  /* Set a default finalTime as 10s to calculate finite buffer size */



5385            if ((finalTime == -1) ||  (finalTime == rtInf))



5386            {



5387                finalTimeTemp = 10;



5388            }



5389            else



5390            {



5391                finalTimeTemp = finalTime;



5392            }



5393



5394            if (sampleTime == -2.0) {  /* The signal being logged is constant,  *



5395             * Hence, only one data point is logged. */



5396                stepSize = finalTimeTemp;



5397            } else if (sampleTime == -1.0 || sampleTime == 0.0) {



5398                /* Signal being logged is either inside a    *



5399                 * triggered sub-system or it is continuous. */



5400                stepSize = inStepSize;



5401            } else {                /* Discrete signal */



5402                stepSize = sampleTime;



5403            }



5404            



5405            if (stepSize == 0.0) {



5406                /* small initial value, so as to exercise the realloc code */



5407                nRows = maxRows+1;



5408                okayToRealloc = 1;



5409            } else {



5410                nPoints = 1.0 + floor((finalTimeTemp-startTime)/stepSize);



5411                



5412                /*



5413                 * Add one more data point if needed.



5414                 */



5415                if ( stepSize*(nPoints-1.0) < (finalTimeTemp-startTime) ) {



5416                    nPoints += 1.0;



5417                }



5418                



5419                /*



5420                 * Actual number of points to log = nPoints * size of



5421                 * each frame if data is frame-based



5422                 */



5423                nPoints = frameData ? (nPoints * frameSize) : nPoints;



5424                



5425                nPoints /= decimation;



5426                if (nPoints != floor(nPoints)) {



5427                    nPoints += 1.0;



5428                }



5429                nRows = (nPoints <= INT_MAX) ? ((int_T) nPoints) : INT_MAX;



5430            }



5431            /*



5432             * If maxRows is specified, and if this number is less



5433             * than the number we computed (nRows) then use maxRows.



5434             */



5435            if ((maxRows > 0) && (maxRows < nRows)) {



5436                nRows = maxRows;



5437                okayToRealloc = 0;



5438            }



5439        } else if (finalTime == startTime) {



5440            /*



5441             * Number of rows to log is equal to 1 if not frame-based and



5442             * equal to frame size if frame-based



5443             */



5444            nRows = frameData ? frameSize : 1;



5445            



5446            /*



5447             * If maxRows is specified, and if this number is less



5448             * than the number we computed (nRows) then use maxRows.



5449             */



5450            if ((maxRows > 0) && (maxRows < nRows)) {



5451                nRows = maxRows;



5452                okayToRealloc = 0;



5453            }



5454        } else if (maxRows > 0) {     /* maxRows is specified => nRows=maxRows  */



5455            nRows = maxRows;



5456            okayToRealloc = 0;



5457        } else {



5458            



5459            if (inStepSize == 0) {



5460                /* small initial value, so as to exercise the realloc code */



5461                nRows = maxRows+1;



5462                okayToRealloc = 1;



5463            } else {                    /* Use a default value for nRows          */



5464                usingDefaultBufSize = 1;



5465                nRows = DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE;



5466                okayToRealloc = 0;  /* No realloc with infinite stop time */



5467                #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5468                statusMessage = DEFAULTBUFFERUSED;



5469                #else



5470                (void)fprintf(stdout, "*** Using a default buffer of size %d for "



5471                        "logging variable %s\n", nRows, varName);



5472                #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5473            }



5474        }



5475        



5476        /*



5477         * Figure out the number of columns that the log variable should have.



5478         * If the data is not frame based, then number of columns should equal



5479         * nCols that is provided as input to the function. If the data is



5480         * frame-based, then the number of columns should be equal to the



5481         * number of channels = nCols/frameSize = dims[1];



5482         */



5483        nColumns = frameData ? dims[1] : nCols;



5484        



5485        /*



5486         * Error out if the size of the circular buffer is absurdly large, this



5487         * error message is more informative than the one we get when we try to



5488         * malloc this many number of bytes in one fell swoop.



5489         */



5490        {



5491            double tmpDbl = ((double)elementSize)*((double)nRows)*



5492                    ((double)nColumns);



5493            



5494            if (tmpDbl >= UINT_MAX) {



5495                #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5496                statusMessage = HUGEMEMORYREQUIRED;



5497                #else



5498                (void)fprintf(stderr,



5499                        "\n*** Memory required to log variable '%s' is too"



5500                        "\n    big. Use the 'Limit rows to last:' and (or)"



5501                        "\n    'Decimation:' options to reduce the required"



5502                        "\n    memory size.\n", varName);



5503                (void)fprintf(stderr, "*** Details:\n"



5504                        "       varName         = %s\n"



5505                        "       nRows           = %d\n"



5506                        "       nCols           = %d\n"



5507                        "       elementSize     = %lu\n"



5508                        "       Bytes Required  = %.16g\n\n",



5509                        varName, nRows, nColumns, (unsigned long)



5510                        elementSize, tmpDbl);



5511                #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5512                goto ERROR_EXIT;



5513            }



5514        }



5515        



5516        /* Allocate memory for the log variable */



5517        #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



5518        if ( (var = staticAlloc(sizeof(LogVar))) == NULL ) {



5519        #else



5520        if ( (var = calloc(1, sizeof(LogVar))) == NULL ) {



5521        #endif



5522            #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5523            statusMessage = LOGVARMEMORYALLOCATIONERROR;



5524            #else



5525            (void)fprintf(stderr, "*** Error allocating memory for logging %s\n",



5526                    varName);



5527            #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5528            goto ERROR_EXIT;



5529        }



5530        



5531        /* Allocate memory for the circular buffer (real part) */



5532        #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



5533        if ( (var->data.re = staticAlloc(nRows*nColumns*elementSize)) == NULL ) {



5534        #else



5535        if ( (var->data.re = malloc(nRows*nColumns*elementSize)) == NULL ) {



5536        #endif



5537            #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5538            statusMessage = ERRORALLOCATINGCIRCULARBUFFER;



5539            #else



5540            (void)fprintf(stderr,



5541                    "*** Error allocating memory for the circular buffer\n");



5542            (void)fprintf(stderr, "*** Details:\n"



5543                    "       varName         = %s\n"



5544                    "       nRows           = %d\n"



5545                    "       nCols           = %d\n"



5546                    "       elementSize     = %lu\n"



5547                    "       Bytes Requested = %.16g\n\n",



5548                    varName, nRows, nColumns, (unsigned long) elementSize,



5549                    ((double)elementSize)*((double)nRows)*((double)nColumns));



5550            #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5551            goto ERROR_EXIT;



5552        }



5553        



5554        /* Allocate memory for the circular buffer for the imaginary part */



5555        if (complex) {



5556            #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



5557            if ( (var->data.im = staticAlloc(nRows*nColumns*elementSize)) == NULL ) {



5558            #else



5559            if ( (var->data.im = malloc(nRows*nColumns*elementSize)) == NULL ) {



5560            #endif



5561                #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5562                statusMessage = ERRORALLOCATINGCIRCULARBUFFER;



5563                #else



5564                (void)fprintf(stderr,



5565                        "*** Error allocating memory for the circular buffer "



5566                        "for logging the imaginary part of %s\n", varName);



5567                (void)fprintf(stderr, "*** Details:\n"



5568                        "       varName         = %s\n"



5569                        "       nRows           = %d\n"



5570                        "       nCols           = %d\n"



5571                        "       elementSize     = %lu\n"



5572                        "       Bytes Requested = %.16g\n\n",



5573                        varName, nRows, nColumns, (unsigned long) elementSize,



5574                        ((double)elementSize)*((double)nRows)*



5575                        ((double)nColumns));



5576                #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5577                goto ERROR_EXIT;



5578            }



5579        }



5580        /*



5581         * Initialize the fields in LogVar structure.



5582         */



5583        if (appendToLogVarsList) {



5584            rt_LoadModifiedLogVarName(li,varName,var->data.name);



5585        } else {



5586            var->data.name[mxMAXNAM-1] = '\0';



5587            (void)strncpy(var->data.name,varName,mxMAXNAM-1);



5588        }



5589        var->data.nCols           = nColumns;



5590        var->data.nRows           = nRows;



5591        



5592        var->data.nDims           = frameData ? 1 : nDims;



5593        if (var->data.nDims > 2) {



5594            #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



5595            var->data.dims = (int_T*)staticAlloc(sizeof(int_T)*var->data.nDims);



5596            #else



5597            var->data.dims = (int_T*)malloc(sizeof(int_T)*var->data.nDims);



5598            #endif



5599        } else {



5600            var->data.dims = var->data._dims;



5601        }



5602        if (frameData) {



5603            var->data.dims[0] = nColumns;



5604        } else {



5605            /*LINTED E_CAST_INT_TO_SMALL_INT*/



5606            (void)memcpy(var->data.dims, dims, (size_t)(nDims*sizeof(int_T)));



5607        }



5608        



5609        var->data.dTypeID         = dTypeID;



5610        var->data.elSize          = elementSize;



5611        



5612        var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo = rt_GetDataTypeConvertInfo(



5613                pDataTypeConvertInfo, dTypeID);



5614        



5615        var->data.mxID            = rt_GetMxIdFromDTypeId(dTypeID);



5616        /* over-ride logical bit if data type is boolean */



5617        logical = dTypeID == SS_BOOLEAN ? 1 : 0;



5618        var->data.logical         = (logical)   ? matLOGICAL_BIT : 0x0;



5619        var->data.complex         = (complex)   ? matCOMPLEX_BIT : 0x0;



5620        var->data.frameData       = frameData;



5621        var->data.frameSize       = (frameData) ? frameSize : 1;



5622        



5623        /* fill up valDims field */



5624        if(logValDimsStat == NO_LOGVALDIMS){



5625            /* All signals are fixed-size, no need to log valueDimensions field */



5626            var->valDims     = NULL;



5627            /* Set these pointers to NULLs in this case */



5628            var->coords      = NULL;



5629            var->strides     = NULL;



5630            var->currStrides = NULL;



5631        }



5632        else{



5633            #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



5634            if ( (var->valDims = staticAlloc(sizeof(ValDimsData))) == NULL ) {



5635            #else



5636            if ( (var->valDims = calloc(1, sizeof(ValDimsData))) == NULL ) {



5637            #endif



5638                goto ERROR_EXIT;



5639            }



5640            



5641            (void)memcpy(var->valDims->name, &VALUEDIMENSIONS_FIELD_NAME, mxMAXNAM);



5642            



5643            if (logValDimsStat == LOGVALDIMS_EMPTYMX) {



5644                /* At least one signal is variable-size,



5645                 * but the current signal is fixed-size.



5646                 * Therefore, create a dummy MatrixData to write out valueDimensions



5647                 * as an empty matrix.



5648                 */



5649                var->valDims->nRows = 0;



5650                var->valDims->nCols = 0;



5651                var->valDims->currSigDims = NULL;



5652                var->valDims->currSigDimsSize = NULL;



5653                var->valDims->dimsData = NULL;



5654                /* Set these pointers to NULLs in this case */



5655                var->coords      = NULL;



5656                var->strides     = NULL;



5657                var->currStrides = NULL;



5658            } else { /* The current signal is a variable-size signal. */



5659                /* The "valueDimensions" must be double, so re-assign element size */



5660                elementSize = sizeof(real_T);



5661                



5662                /* When signals are frame-based, 'valueDimensions' has 1 column */



5663                if(frameData){



5664                    /* When signal is frame-based, the first dimension is always fixed,



5665                     * so we only need to record the second dimension.



5666                     * e.g. Two frame-based signals [10x4] and [10x3],



5667                     * 'valueDimensions' and 'currSigDims'



5668                     * only record 4 or 3.



5669                     */



5670                    nColumns = 1;



5671                    var->valDims->currSigDims = (void**) (currSigDims + 1);



5672                    var->valDims->currSigDimsSize = (int_T*) (currSigDimsSize + 1);



5673                } else { /* non-frame based */



5674                    nColumns = nDims;



5675                    var->valDims->currSigDims = (void**) currSigDims;



5676                    var->valDims->currSigDimsSize = (int_T*) currSigDimsSize;



5677                }



5678                



5679                /* Allocate memory for the circular buffer */



5680                #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



5681                if ( (var->valDims->dimsData = staticAlloc(nRows*nColumns*elementSize)) == NULL ) {



5682                #else



5683                if ( (var->valDims->dimsData = malloc(nRows*nColumns*elementSize)) == NULL ) {



5684                #endif



5685                    #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5686                    statusMessage = ERRORALLOCATINGCIRCULARBUFFER;



5687                    #else



5688                    (void)fprintf(stderr,



5689                            "*** Error allocating memory for the circular buffer\n");



5690                    (void)fprintf(stderr, "*** Details:\n"



5691                            "       varName         = %s\n"



5692                            "       nRows           = %d\n"



5693                            "       nCols           = %d\n"



5694                            "       elementSize     = %lu\n"



5695                            "       Bytes Requested = %.16g\n\n",



5696                            var->valDims->name, nRows, nColumns, (unsigned long) elementSize,



5697                            ((double)elementSize)*((double)nRows)*((double)nColumns));



5698                    #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



5699                    goto ERROR_EXIT;



5700                }



5701                var->valDims->nRows = nRows;



5702                var->valDims->nCols = nColumns;



5703                



5704                /* Allocate memory for these dynamic arrays */



5705                {



5706                    size_t nbytes = var->data.nDims*sizeof(int_T);



5707                    #ifdef MW_SD_STATIC_MEMORY_ENABLE



5708                    if( ((var->coords = staticAlloc(nbytes)) == NULL)



5709                    ||((var->strides = staticAlloc(nbytes)) == NULL)



5710                    ||((var->currStrides = staticAlloc(nbytes)) == NULL) )



5711                    #else



5712                    if( ((var->coords = calloc(nbytes, 1)) == NULL)



5713                    ||((var->strides = calloc(nbytes, 1)) == NULL)



5714                    ||((var->currStrides = calloc(nbytes, 1)) == NULL) )



5715                    #endif



5716                        goto ERROR_EXIT;



5717                }



5718            }



5719        }



5720        



5721        var->rowIdx               = 0;



5722        var->wrapped              = 0;



5723        var->nDataPoints          = 0;



5724        var->usingDefaultBufSize  = usingDefaultBufSize;



5725        var->okayToRealloc        = okayToRealloc;



5726        var->decimation           = decimation;



5727        var->numHits              = -1;  /* so first point gets logged */



5728        



5729        /* Add this log var to list in log info, if necessary */



5730        if (appendToLogVarsList) {



5731            LogInfo *logInfo = (LogInfo*) rtliGetLogInfo(li);



5732            LogVar  *varList = logInfo->logVarsList;



5733            



5734            if (varList != NULL) {



5735                while (varList->next != NULL) {



5736                    varList = varList->next;



5737                }



5738                varList->next = var;

5751            #endif

5887    /* Function: rt_StartDataLoggingWithStartTime ==================================

5892     * Return value is:



5893     *	== NULL  => success



5894     *	!= NULL  => failure (the return value is a pointer that points to the



5895     *                           error message, which is also set in the simstruct)

5897    const char_T *rt_StartDataLoggingWithStartTime(RTWLogInfo   *li,



5898            const real_T startTime,



5899            const real_T finalTime,



5900            const real_T stepSize,

5918        #endif

5920            *errStatus = rtMemAllocError;



5921            goto ERROR_EXIT;



5922        }



5923



5924        rtliSetLogInfo(li, (void*)logInfo);



5925

5929            int_T dims = 1;

5931                    stepSize, errStatus,

5933                    NULL,



5934                    0,0,0,1,1,



5935                    &dims, NO_LOGVALDIMS, NULL, NULL,



5936                    maxRows,decimation,



5937                    sampleTime,1);



5938            if (logInfo->t == NULL) goto ERROR_EXIT;



5939        }



5940        



5941        /* states */



5942        if ( rtliGetLogX(li)[0] != '\0' ||  rtliGetLogXFinal(li)[0] != '\0' ) {

5985                            stepSize, errStatus,



5986                            rtliGetLogXFinal(li),dataType,



5987                            pDTConvInfo,



5988                            0,isComplex,0,numCols,nDims,



5989                            dims, NO_LOGVALDIMS, NULL,



5990                            NULL, 1,decimation,



5991                            sampleTime,1);



5992                    if (logInfo->xFinal == NULL)  goto ERROR_EXIT;



5993                }



5994            } else {                                          /* Structure Format */



5995                if (rtliGetLogX(li)[0] != '\0') {



5996                    logInfo->x = local_CreateStructLogVar(li, startTime, finalTime,



5997                            stepSize, errStatus,



5998                            rtliGetLogX(li), logTime,



5999                            maxRows, decimation,



6000                            sampleTime, xInfo, NULL);



6001                    if (logInfo->x == NULL) goto ERROR_EXIT;



6002                }

6020        



6021        ERROR_EXIT:



6022



6023                    #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE

6025                    #else



6026                    (void)fprintf(stderr, "*** Errors occurred when starting data logging.\n");



6027                    #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



6028                    if (*errStatus == NULL) {



6029                        *errStatus = rtMemAllocError;



6030                    }



6031                    if (logInfo) {

6084    /* Function: rt_UpdateLogVar ===================================================



6085     * Abstract:



6086     *	Called to log data for a log variable.



6087     */



6088    void rt_UpdateLogVar(LogVar *var, const void *data, boolean_T isVarDims)



6089    {



6090        if(bStopLogging ==0)



6091        {



6092            size_t        elSize    = var->data.elSize;



6093            const  char_T *cData    = data;



6094            const  int_T  frameData = var->data.frameData;



6095            const  int_T  frameSize = frameData ? (var->data.frameSize) : 1;



6096            const  int_T  logWidth  = var->data.nCols;



6097            BuiltInDTypeId dTypeID  = var->data.dTypeID;



6098            



6099            size_t offset        = 0;



6100            char_T *currRealRow  = NULL;



6101            char_T *currImagRow  = NULL;



6102            int_T  pointSize     = (int_T)((var->data.complex) ? rt_GetSizeofComplexType(dTypeID) : elSize);



6103            



6104            int    i, j, k;



6105            



6106            /* The following variables will be used for



6107             * logging variable-size signals */



6108            const  int_T  nDims = var->data.nDims;



6109            const  int_T  *dims = var->data.dims;



6110            const  void   * const *currDimsPtr = NULL;



6111            const  int_T  *currDimsSizePtr = NULL;



6112            



6113            /* The following variables will be used for



6114             * logging "valueDimensions" field */



6115            size_t offset_valDims   = 0;



6116            char_T *currValDimsRow  = NULL;



6117            size_t elSize_valDims   = sizeof(real_T);



6118            real_T currentSigDims   = 0;



6119            int_T  nRows_valDims    = 0;



6120            int_T  logWidth_valDims = 0;



6121            



6122            



6123            for (i = 0; i < frameSize; i++) {



6124                if (++var->numHits % var->decimation) continue;



6125                var->numHits = 0;



6126                



6127                if (((var->rowIdx == ((var->data.nRows)/2)) && !(var->wrapped == var->data.nRows+1)) || ((var->rowIdx == var->data.nRows) && !(var->wrapped == -1))) {



6128                    /* Check the wrapped variable to ensure that the bDataReady is not getting triggered by the var which missed bDataReady before */



6129                    bDataReady = 1;



6130                }



6131                



6132                if(bDataReady ==1) /* switching to the other half of the ping-pong */



6133                {



6134                    if (var->wrapped == -2)



6135                    {



6136                        var->rowIdx = 0; /* Needs to switch to ping, this var didn't see bDataReady */



6137                        var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



6138                    }



6139                    else if ((!((var->wrapped == -1) || (var->wrapped == (var->data.nRows + 1)) ))&& ((var->wrapped < (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx < (var->data.nRows)/2))) /* wrapped and rowIdx are in the ping */



6140                    {



6141                        var->rowIdx = ((var->data.nRows)/2); /* switching to pong */



6142                    }



6143                    else if ((!((var->wrapped == -1) || (var->wrapped == (var->data.nRows + 1)) )) && ((var->wrapped >= (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx >= (var->data.nRows)/2))) /* wrapped and rowIdx are in the pong */



6144                    {



6145                        var->rowIdx = 0; /* switching to ping */



6146                    }



6147                    else if (((var->wrapped < (var->data.nRows)/2)  || (var->wrapped == (var->data.nRows + 1))) && (var->rowIdx == var->data.nRows)) /* check if the rowIdx is not crossing boundaries */



6148                    {



6149                        var->rowIdx = (var->data.nRows)/2;



6150                    }



6151                    else if (((var->wrapped >= (var->data.nRows)/2) || (var->wrapped == -1)) && (var->rowIdx == var->data.nRows/2)) /*check if the rowIdx is not crossing boundaries */



6152                    {



6153                        var->rowIdx = 0;



6154                    }



6155                }



6156                else if (var->wrapped == -2)



6157                {



6158                    var->rowIdx = 0; /* Needs to switch to ping, this var didn't see bDataReady */



6159                    var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



6160                }



6161                else if ((var->wrapped < (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx >= (var->data.nRows)/2)) /* wrapped is in the ping, rowIdx in the pong */



6162                {



6163                    var->rowIdx = 0; /* Needs to switch to ping, this var didn't see bDataReady */



6164                    var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



6165                }



6166                else if ((var->wrapped >= (var->data.nRows)/2) && (var->rowIdx < (var->data.nRows)/2)) /* wrapped is in the pong, rowIdx in the ping */



6167                {



6168                    var->rowIdx = ((var->data.nRows)/2); /* Needs to switch to pong, this var didn't see bDataReady */



6169                    var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



6170                }



6171                else



6172                {



6173                    var->wrapped = var->rowIdx; //Store the row Index before wrapped



6174                }



6175                



6176                if(isVarDims){



6177                    currDimsPtr = (const void * const *) var->valDims->currSigDims;



6178                    currDimsSizePtr = (const int_T*) var->valDims->currSigDimsSize;



6179                    logWidth_valDims = frameData ? 1 : var->valDims->nCols;



6180                    nRows_valDims = var->valDims->nRows;



6181                    



6182                    var->strides[0] = 1;



6183                    var->currStrides[0] = 1;



6184                    



6185                    for (k = 1; k < nDims; k++){



6186                        int32_T currDimsVal=0;



6187                        switch (currDimsSizePtr[k-1]) {



6188                            case 1:



6189                                currDimsVal = (**(((const uint8_T * const *) currDimsPtr)+(k-1)));



6190                                break;



6191                            case 2:



6192                                currDimsVal = (**(((const uint16_T * const *) currDimsPtr)+(k-1)));



6193                                break;



6194                            case 4:



6195                                currDimsVal = (**(((const uint32_T * const *) currDimsPtr)+(k-1)));



6196                                break;



6197                        }



6198                        var->strides[k] = var->strides[k-1] * dims[k-1];



6199                        var->currStrides[k] = var->currStrides[k-1] * currDimsVal;



6200                    }



6201                }



6202                



6203                offset       = (size_t)(elSize * var->rowIdx * logWidth);



6204                currRealRow  = ((char_T*) (var->data.re)) + offset;



6205                currImagRow  = (var->data.complex) ?



6206                    ((char_T*) (var->data.im)) + offset :  NULL;



6207                    



6208                    /* update logging data */



6209                    for (j = 0; j < logWidth; j++) {



6210                        



6211                        boolean_T inRange = true;



6212                        int idx = j;



6213                        



6214                        /* Check whether the currently logged value is in range or not.



6215                         * For fixed-size signal logging, always inRange = true; idx = j;



6216                         * For variable-size signal logging, use strides, coordinates



6217                         * and current strides to decide whether the currently logged



6218                         * data is in range or not and its location in the logging



6219                         * matrix.



6220                         */



6221                        if(isVarDims){



6222                            int rem = j;



6223                            idx = 0;



6224                            for(k = nDims-1; k>=0; k--){



6225                                int32_T currDimsVal=0;



6226                                switch (currDimsSizePtr[k]) {



6227                                    case 1:



6228                                        currDimsVal = (**(((const uint8_T * const *) currDimsPtr)+k));



6229                                        break;



6230                                    case 2:



6231                                        currDimsVal = (**(((const uint16_T * const *) currDimsPtr)+k));



6232                                        break;



6233                                    case 4:



6234                                        currDimsVal = (**(((const uint32_T * const *) currDimsPtr)+k));



6235                                        break;



6236                                }



6237                                var->coords[k] = rem / var->strides[k];



6238                                if( var->coords[k] >= currDimsVal ){



6239                                    inRange = false;



6240                                    break;



6241                                }



6242                                rem = rem - var->coords[k] * var->strides[k];



6243                            }



6244                            if(inRange){



6245                                idx = var->coords[0];



6246                                for (k = 1; k < nDims; k++){



6247                                    idx += var->coords[k] * var->currStrides[k];



6248                                }



6249                            }



6250                        }



6251                        



6252                        if (!var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.conversionNeeded) {



6253                            /* NO  conversion needed



6254                             */



6255                            if (inRange) {



6256                                /* If in range, fill in data */



6257                                const char *cDataPoint = cData + (i+frameSize*idx) * pointSize;



6258                                



6259                                (void) memcpy(currRealRow, cDataPoint, elSize);



6260                                currRealRow += elSize;



6261                                if (var->data.complex) {



6262                                    (void) memcpy(currImagRow, cDataPoint + pointSize/2, elSize);



6263                                    currImagRow += elSize;



6264                                }



6265                            } else {



6266                                /* If out of range, fill in NaN or 0:



6267                                 * 1) For bool, int32, uint32, int16, uint16, etc,



6268                                 * memset to zeros;



6269                                 * 2) For fixed-point data type, NaN conversion is not



6270                                 * allowed, memset to zeros.



6271                                 */



6272                                if (dTypeID == SS_DOUBLE) {



6273                                    if(sizeof(real_T) == sizeof(real32_T))



6274                                    {



6275                                        (void) memcpy(currRealRow, &rtNaNF, elSize);



6276                                    }



6277                                    else



6278                                    {



6279                                        (void) memcpy(currRealRow, &rtNaN, elSize);



6280                                    }



6281                                } else if (dTypeID == SS_SINGLE){



6282                                    (void) memcpy(currRealRow, &rtNaNF, elSize);



6283                                } else {



6284                                    (void) memset(currRealRow, 0, elSize);



6285                                }



6286                                



6287                                currRealRow += elSize;



6288                                if (var->data.complex) {



6289                                    /* For imaginary part, fill in 0 */



6290                                    (void) memset(currImagRow, 0, elSize);



6291                                    currImagRow += elSize;



6292                                }



6293                            }



6294                        }



6295                        else



6296                        {



6297                            /* YES conversion needed



6298                             */



6299                            DTypeId dataTypeIdOriginal =



6300                                    var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.dataTypeIdOriginal;



6301                            int_T DpSize = (int_T)((var->data.complex) ?



6302                                rt_GetSizeofComplexType(dataTypeIdOriginal) :



6303                                rt_GetSizeofDataType(dataTypeIdOriginal));



6304                                



6305                                DTypeId dataTypeIdLoggingTo =



6306                                        var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.dataTypeIdLoggingTo;



6307                                



6308                                int bitsPerChunk = var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.bitsPerChunk;



6309                                int numOfChunk =  var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.numOfChunk;



6310                                unsigned int isSigned = var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.isSigned;



6311                                



6312                                double fracSlope = var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.fracSlope;



6313                                int    fixedExp  = var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.fixedExp;



6314                                double bias      = var->data.dataTypeConvertInfo.bias;



6315                                



6316                                double curRealValue = -0.12345678987654;



6317                                double curImagValue = -0.12345678987654;



6318                                



6319                                int_T adjIndexIfComplex = (var->data.complex) ? 2 : 1;



6320                                



6321                                if(inRange){



6322                                    if(numOfChunk > 1)



6323                                    {



6324                                        /* For multiword */



6325                                        const char *pInData = (const char *)(cData);



6326                                        int dtSize = bitsPerChunk*numOfChunk/8;



6327                                        pInData += ((i+frameSize*idx) * adjIndexIfComplex) * dtSize;



6328                                        



6329                                        curRealValue = rt_GetDblValueFromOverSizedData(pInData, bitsPerChunk, numOfChunk,



6330                                                isSigned, fracSlope, fixedExp, bias);



6331                                        if (var->data.complex) {



6332                                            curImagValue = rt_GetDblValueFromOverSizedData((pInData+dtSize), bitsPerChunk, numOfChunk,



6333                                                    isSigned, fracSlope, fixedExp, bias);



6334                                        }



6335                                    }



6336                                    else



6337                                    {



6338                                        /* if in range, fill in data that is converted first */

7079    /* Function: rt_StopDataLogging ================================================



7080     * Abstract:



7081     *	Write logged data to model.mat and free memory.
