7083    void rt_StopDataLogging(const char_T *file, RTWLogInfo *li)



7084    {



7085        #ifdef MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7086        static char newfilename[256];



7087        static char numstr_file[16] = "_";



7088        static char numstr_run[16] = "_";



7089        #else



7090        int8_T newfilename[256],numstr_file[256],numstr_run[256];



7091        #endif //MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7092        char extn[10] = ".mat";



7093        uint32_T len = 0;



7094        static uint32_T file_index=1;



7095        static uint32_T run_index=1;



7096        static uint8_T firstTime =1;



7097        static int8_T filename[256];



7098        



7099        



7100        FILE *result;



7101        



7102        if((stopRequested == 1) && (bStopLogging ==0))



7103        {



7104            bDataReady =1;            



7105        }



7106        



7107        if(bDataReady ==1)



7108        {



7109            if (firstTime)



7110            {



7111                /* Remove the .mat from filename */



7112                len = strlen(file)-4;



7113                /* memset the filename holders to 0 */



7114                memset(newfilename,0,256);



7115                memset(filename,0,256);



7116                /* Prepend pathName */



7117                memcpy(filename,file,len);



7118                /* make a copy of the filename */



7119                memcpy(newfilename,filename,strlen((const char *)filename));



7120                #ifdef MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7121                itoa(file_index, (char *)(numstr_file+1), 10) ;



7122                itoa(run_index, (char *)(numstr_run+1), 10) ;



7123                #else



7124                sprintf((char *)numstr_file,"%d",file_index);



7125                sprintf((char *)numstr_run,"_%d_",run_index);



7126                #endif //MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7127                strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)numstr_run);



7128                strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)numstr_file);



7129                strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)extn);



7130                



7131                while((result=MW_fopen((const char *)newfilename,"r")))



7132                {



7133                    MW_fclose(result);



7134                    run_index++;



7135                    memset(newfilename,0,strlen((const char *)newfilename));



7136                    memcpy(newfilename,file,len);



7137                    #ifdef MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7138                    itoa(file_index, (char *)(numstr_file+1), 10) ;



7139                    itoa(run_index, (char *)(numstr_run+1), 10) ;



7140                    #else



7141                    sprintf((char *)numstr_file,"%d",file_index);



7142                    sprintf((char *)numstr_run,"_%d_",run_index);



7143                    #endif //MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7144                    strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)numstr_run);



7145                    strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)numstr_file);



7146                    strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)extn);



7147                }



7148                firstTime = 0;



7149            }



7150            else



7151            {



7152                file_index++;



7153                memset(newfilename,0,256);



7154                memcpy(newfilename,filename,strlen((const char *)filename));



7155                #ifdef MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7156                itoa(file_index, (char *)(numstr_file+1), 10) ;



7157                itoa(run_index, (char *)(numstr_run+1), 10) ;



7158                #else



7159                sprintf((char *)numstr_file,"%d",file_index);



7160                sprintf((char *)numstr_run,"_%d_",run_index);



7161                #endif //MW_SD_LOW_STACK_MEMORY



7162                strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)numstr_run);



7163                strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)numstr_file);



7164                strcat((char *)newfilename,(char *)extn);



7165            }



7166            rt_StopDataLoggingImpl((char *)newfilename,li,false);



7167            bDataReady =0;



7168            if((stopRequested == 1) && (bStopLogging ==0))



7169            {



7170                bStopLogging = 1;



7171            }



7172            #ifdef MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



7173            fileNumber = file_index;



7174            runNumber = run_index;



7175            #endif //MW_SD_VERBOSE_DISABLE



7176        }
